# [0.1.0] - Initial Framework Release

## Added

### Project Foundation

* Initial repository structure established.
* Modular PowerShell architecture defined.
* Documentation framework completed.
* Semantic versioning adopted.
* Standard repository layout implemented.

### Documentation

Added the following project documentation:

* README.md
* ARCHITECTURE.md
* DATABASE.md
* DEVELOPMENT.md
* CONTRIBUTING.md
* CHANGELOG.md

### Core Architecture

Defined the initial architecture consisting of:

* Core framework
* Logging engine
* Inventory engine
* Reporting engine
* SQLite database layer
* Plugin discovery architecture
* Configuration management subsystem

### Database Design

Initial relational database model designed.

Core entities include:

* Assets
* TechnicalChecks
* TechnicalEvidence
* Frameworks
* Controls
* FrameworkMappings
* Vulnerabilities
* STIGFindings
* SCAPResults
* POAM
* Risks
* ScanHistory

### Repository Layout

Established standard project structure.

```text
SentinelGRC/

Assets/

Checks/

Config/

Database/

Docs/

FrameworkMappings/

Logs/

Modules/

Reports/

Samples/

SQL/

Tests/

Tools/

Invoke-SentinelGRC.ps1

Install.ps1
```

### Development Standards

Defined project-wide standards for:

* PowerShell naming conventions
* Module organization
* Logging
* Error handling
* Testing
* Documentation
* Database migrations
* Branch strategy
* Pull request workflow

### Coding Standards

Established:

* Approved PowerShell verbs
* One responsibility per module
* One compliance check per script
* Standardized compliance object model
* JSON-based configuration
* SQLite as the authoritative data source

### Design Goals

Established the following architectural principles:

* Collect evidence once.
* Normalize technical evidence.
* Separate evidence collection from framework mappings.
* Support multiple compliance frameworks from a single technical check.
* Maintain vendor neutrality.
* Favor modular expansion over monolithic development.

